Question: A good way to develop your delegation technique is to solicit feedback from others.

What are some best practices for getting feedback on your delegation style?
Instruction: Choose all options that best answer the question. 

Offer to reciprocate and provide feedback on team members' performance

Give people the chance to provide feedback privately or in confidence

Insist on honest, open discussion in a public forum

Assemble the feedback and consider it in its entirety

Ensure your team understands the importance of feedback

Ask leading questions to solicit insightful information
